      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here's a revised version with a bit more warmth and personality:\n\nDear Marcus,\n\nI wanted to personally reach out to you and express our gratitude for the time you took to interview with us for the Senior Developer position at our Austin office. We were truly impressed by your technical skills and overall fit for the role. Your passion for distributed systems and innovative approach to problem-solving really stood out to us, and we appreciated the effort you put into preparing for the interview.\n\nAfter careful consideration, we've decided to move forward with another candidate whose experience aligns more closely with our current needs. Please know that this decision wasn't made lightly, and we were genuinely impressed by your abilities. We think you'd be a great fit for many teams, and we're confident you'll find a great opportunity that aligns with your skills and interests.\n\nWe'd love to keep in touch and offer you a reference, if you'd like. We're always happy to sing the praises of talented candidates like yourself, and we're confident that you'll make a significant impact in your future endeavors.\n\nThanks again for your interest in our team, and we wish you all the best in your job search.\n\nBest regards,\n[Your Name]\n\nThis version aims to be a bit more",
